Decision
--------
Do not promote in-stage layer-wavefront scheduling. The diagnostic is correct
and default-off, but same-prompt 16-slot/256K A/B shows it loses materially
against the existing per-step event-handoff baseline. Chunk 4 is worse than
chunk 2, so the extra same-layer batching does not recover enough kernel
density to offset scheduling/serialization overhead.

Next
----
Stop spending near-term effort on layer-parallel slot scheduling. The next
material path should be a broader persistent TP/EP scheduler boundary or a
DS4-specific persistent routed-FFN executor that keeps packed MXFP4 dequant,
gate/up HMMA, gated activation, down HMMA, and weighted reduction inside a
single long-lived execution boundary.

